HEADWORD: Seannachie
<hw>Sean"na*chie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael.
<ets>seanachaidh</ets>.]</ety> <def>A bard among the Highlanders of
Scotland, who preserved and repeated the traditions of the tribes; also,
a genealogist.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>sennachy</asp>.]</altsp>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sea onion</ent>⟦br⟧
